# File:         main.py
# Description:  This lab is an introduction to input using Kivy text input,
#               Python variables and operators
# Input:        This program has 2 numerical inputs, 'Rate' and 'Hours'
# Output:       Display the product of the 2 numbers using a Calculate button.
# Processing:   The Calculate Button releases the event function.
#               Declare input variables Pay Rate and Hours Worked to hold integer input from the text input boxes.
#               Cast both Rate and Hours as a float.
#               If: ‘Hours’ > 40,
#               Gross Pay = ((rate * 1.5) * (hours - 40)) + (rate * 40)
#               Else: Gross Pay = Pay Rate * Hours Worked
#               Convert result to string and format 2 decimal places.
#               Display in the Gross Pay label.
#
#               The Exit button releases the event function.
#               Stop the application.

# Density-independent Pixels - An abstract unit based on the physical density of the screen.
# With a density of 1, 1dp is equal to 1px. When running on a higher density screen, the number of
# pixels used to draw 1dp is scaled up a factor appropriate to the screen’s dpi, and the inverse
# for a lower dpi.
# Scale-independent Pixels - This is like the dp unit,
# but it is also scaled by the user’s font size preference. See examples below:
# font_size: '16dp'
# font_size: sp(16)
# font_size: dp(16)
# height: dp(50)

<MyLayout>:

    GridLayout:
        cols: 2
        size: root.width, root.height
        padding: dp(50)
        spacing: dp(50)

        Label:
            text: 'Pay Rate'
            font_size: dp(16)
            size_hint_x: 1      # in percentage, 1 is 100%
            size_hint_y: None   # no hint from GridLayout
            height: dp(50)

        TextInput:
            id: rate
            text: '10'
            font_size: dp(16)
            size_hint_x: 1
            size_hint_y: None
            height: dp(50)

        Label:
            text: 'Hours Worked'
            font_size: dp(16)
            size_hint_x: 1
            size_hint_y: None
            height: dp(50)

        TextInput:
            id: hours
            text: '20'
            font_size: dp(16)
            size_hint_x: 1
            size_hint_y: None
            height: dp(50)

        Label:
            text: 'Gross Pay'
            font_size: dp(16)
            size_hint_x: 1
            size_hint_y: None
            height: dp(50)

        Label:
            id: grossPay
            text: '$0.00'
            font_size: dp(16)
            size_hint_x: 1
            size_hint_y: None
            height: dp(50)

        Button:
            text: 'Calculate'
            font_size: dp(16)
            size_hint_x: 1
            size_hint_y: None
            height: dp(50)
            # use root instead of app if button event function is in MyLayout
            on_release: app.calculate_button()

        Button:
            text: 'Exit'
            font_size: dp(16)
            size_hint_x: 1
            size_hint_y: None
            height: dp(50)
            # use root instead of app if button event function is in MyLayout
            on_release: app.exit_button()
